<directive id="go-directives">
    <rule>
        Go files MUST adhere to the following sub-directives.
    </rule>
    <sub-directive id="main-function">
        1. The main Function
        1A. The entry point in the should be the main function in the main.go file.
        1B. The main function should call another function called run that returns an error if unsuccessful.
        1C. The main function should exit with a non-zero error if the run function returns an error. 
    </sub-directive>
    <sub-directive id="naming-convention">
        Follow Go naming convention. 
    </sub-directive>
</directive>


